$ \\tau- $ and $ \\mu$-lumps could possibly explain the presence of\nmassive compact objects in galactic centers, and $ \\tau$-lumps could be related\nto globular clusters and the halo mass. This might provide a theoretical\nexplanation for the mass gap between stellar and super massive black holes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Aug 2021 18:52:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-06"}
